Sentencas: Ni electrodes impregnated with nanosized electrocatalytic active (Gd, Ce) O-2 (GDC) particles were fabricated and investigated as anodes for H-2 oxidation reaction in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Performance of GDC-impregnated Ni anodes of SOFCs

Sentencas: Incorporation of nanosized ionic conducting GDC particles significantly reduced the electrode interface resistance and polarization potential.
Titulo: Performance of GDC-impregnated Ni anodes of SOFCs

Sentencas: With the impregnation of 8.5 vol % GDC in Ni anodes, the electrode interface resistance was 0.71 Omega cm(2) at 800 degreesC, close to the good performance value of 0.24 Omega cm(2) reported on Ni (50 vol %)/ YSZ (50 vol %) cermet anodes at the same temperature.
Titulo: Performance of GDC-impregnated Ni anodes of SOFCs

Sentencas: Nanosized GDC particles were deposited on the surface of Ni grains, forming a thin and uniform GDC layer.
Titulo: Performance of GDC-impregnated Ni anodes of SOFCs

Sentencas: Such a unique microstructure shows a potential application as direct methane oxidation anodes for SOFCs based on natural gas fuel.
Titulo: Performance of GDC-impregnated Ni anodes of SOFCs
